		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Konami games set the IRQ timeout (which is CPU cycle based) at the beginning of the vblank period.  PAL NES has a longer vblank time, so it triggers much sooner than it would on an NTSC NES.  So it will split scroll at the wrong time, bankswitch graphics at the wrong time, etc.
<br />
<br />Tepples recommended using an NTSC NES, so there would be no glitches within the game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


