	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I didn't know there was a Hong Kong Famicom.  But doing a quick Google search seems to turn it up in at least one place.  I'd only seen the official HK NES, and their distinctive light grey carts.  
<br />
<br />I have a PAL Famiclone, one time I had a chance to test with expansion sound (Namco106) and it sounded pretty bad because of it being out of tune with the internal channels.  So if that's the case, that actually would explain why the sound would be left unwired.  Though I don't think Lagrange Point does much tone-wise with the internal channels, so that kinda sucks.
<br />
<br />And regarding the "timing sensitive IRQs", that's because it uses CPU cycles for the IRQ timing, so yeah it'd be screwed on PAL mode.  Unlike MMC3, which is more tied to the PPU's scanlines.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


